---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { withBase } from '../utils/url';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Strider Settgast"
  description="Physics undergraduate at Florida Institute of Technology, working on inverse problems, signal processing, and MHD wave localization."
>
  <div class="container">
    <header class="page-header">
      <h1>About</h1>
      <p>What I work on, and why.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        I'm a physics undergraduate at the Florida Institute of Technology,
        minoring in computational mathematics and graduating in 2027. Most of
        what I do comes down to one problem I find endlessly interesting: how
        do you pull a real signal out of noisy data — and how do you know it's
        actually real?
      </p>

      <p>
        Right now that means leading research on magnetohydrodynamic waves,
        using a method called inverse beamforming to locate their sources from
        the faint traces they leave in ground-based magnetometer readings. I
        derived the underlying math, built the full pipeline in Python, and
        found clear evidence that the signal is genuinely global rather
        than local noise. A first-author paper is on the way.
      </p>

      <p>
        What I find compelling is that the same mathematics turns up
        everywhere. The tools that locate a wave source in geomagnetic data
        are, underneath, the tools that decode a brain signal from an EEG or
        find structure in a financial time series. I came to physics for the
        equations and stayed for that strange unity — the sense that signal
        processing, inverse problems, and probability are one language spoken
        in many places. I'm most at home where those overlap, and I'd rather
        follow the mathematics into a new domain than stay put in one.
      </p>

      <p>
        When I'm not doing that, I'm writing about what I'm learning — which
        is mostly what this site is for.
      </p>

      <p class="credentials">
        B.S. Physics &amp; Computational Mathematics, Florida Institute of
        Technology · Expected 2027 · GPA 3.89 · Sigma Pi Sigma
      </p>

      <div class="links">
        <a href={withBase('/cv-strider-settgast.pdf')} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Read my full CV (PDF) →
        </a>
        <a href={withBase('/projects')}>
          See my projects →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }

  .page-header {
    padding: 4rem 0 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .page-header p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .prose {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #333;
    max-width: 640px;
    padding: 2.5rem 0 4rem;
  }

  .prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
  }

  .credentials {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem !important;
  }

  .links {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .links a {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .links a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
</style>
